==English==
===Etymology===
Old English: funel, fonel, prob. through Old French. fr, L.
fundibulum, infundibulum, funnel, fr. infundere to pour in;
in in + fundere to pour; cf. Armor. founil funnel, W. ffynel
air hole, chimney. See [[fuse|Fuse]]

===Pronunciation===
